@page
@model MyPortfolio.Pages.PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="page-hero">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: May 2026</p>
</div>

<section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
        <div class="prose">
            <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We collect information you provide directly to us, such as when you create an account, fill out a form, or contact us. This includes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Name and email address</li>
                <li>Gender and profile information</li>
                <li>Messages and communications you send us</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect to provide, maintain, and improve our services. Specifically:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>To create and manage your account</li>
                <li>To respond to your comments and questions</li>
                <li>To send you updates and notifications</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. Information Security</h2>
            <p>We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no internet transmission is completely secure.</p>

            <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
            <p>We use session cookies to maintain your login state. These cookies are essential for the website to function and are deleted when you close your browser or log out.</p>

            <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>We do not sell, trade, or share your personal data with third parties except as described in this policy or with your consent.</p>

            <h2>6. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <a href="/Contact" style="color:var(--primary);">our contact page</a>.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
